  Primary data source   Query NIST Bibliographic Database for Fe II (new window)
 Nave and Johansson 2013      The present level list, based on Nave and Johansson 2013 , contains only the energy levels identified by these authors in the laboratory spectra of hollow cathode discharges. In addition to this list, Castelli and Kurucz 2010 found several tens of highly excited levels by analyzing spectra of the star HR 6000. These levels need further experimental confirmation in laboratory experiments. They can be found in the extended list of Kurucz.

    Two level intervals within the 3d64s a 6D ground term, 6D3/2-6D1/2 = 114.43838(6) cm-1 and 6D5/2-6D3/2 = 194.92813(4) cm-1, were measured by Brown et al. 1998 using the laser magnetic resonance method. These measured intervals were not included by Nave and Johansson in their level optimization. For consistency with energy levels derived by Nave and Johansson 2013 , we have retained their less accurate values 114.4380(5) and 194.9289(5) cm-1, respectively, for these intervals.

    All Landé factors are quoted from the compilation of Sugar and Corliss 1985 .

    Percentage compositions of wavefunctions for all even levels and odd levels below 106000 cm-1 are from the calculations of Raassen and Uylings 1998 made with the orthogonal operators method. These calculations did not include the 3d66p and several other highly excited configurations observed experimentally. Percentage compositions of the levels above 106000 cm-1 were determined by a parametric fitting of all known odd-parity levels with Cowan's codes (A. Kramida, unpublished, 2013). The additional quantum numbers of the repeating terms of the 3dn subshells, required to uniquely identify the quantum states, were also found in this calculation. These quantum numbers are the Nielson and Koster indexes tabulated by Martin et al. 1978 . In the parametric calculation, theoretical eigenstates were identified with observed energy levels by comparing the predicted and observed sets of transitions and their intensities. As a result, for 68 levels the configuration and term labels given by Nave and Johansson 2013 were changed in the present list.

    As noted by Sugar and Corliss 1985 , the 3d54s4p configuration is best described by the 3d5(S1L1)+4s4p(S2L2°) S3L3 coupling. Thus, the levels of this configuration are labeled in this coupling scheme. However, the percentage compositions of these levels are given in the 3d54s(S1L1)+4p(2P°) SL coupling as used by Raassen and Uylings 1998 . The 3d6nf,g,h configurations are best described in the jK coupling scheme, otherwise called J1l, in which the total angular momentum J1 of the core is coupled with the orbital momentum l of the valence electron to produce an intermediate momentum K, which finally couples with the spin of the valence electron to produce the total angular momentum J. These levels are labeled in this coupling scheme. However, the percentage compositions of the 3d64f configuration, quoted from Raassen and Uylings 1998 , are given in the LS coupling.

    Many energy levels have highly mixed compositions from different interacting configurations. For such levels, the configuration and term labels have little physical meaning. A somewhat better description is provided by the eigenvector compositions given here.
